Linux for DevOps
🔹 Linux Kya Hai?
Linux ek open-source operating system hai jo servers, cloud aur DevOps me use hota hai.
👉 Interview Line:
Linux is an open-source OS widely used in servers and DevOps for automation and stability.
🔹 Short History
•	Unix → 1970s (base system)
•	1991 → Linus Torvalds ne Linux banaya
•	Open-source → free use & modify
🔹Important of Linux in DevOps
•	Almost sab tools Linux pe run karte hain
•	Automation (bash scripting)
•	Server management
•	Troubleshooting
👉 Interview Line:
Linux is the backbone of DevOps because most tools run on it.
🔹 Linux Features
•	Open source
•	Multi-user
•	Multi-tasking
•	Secure
•	Stable
•	Powerful CLI
🔹 Linux vs Windows
•	Linux → servers / DevOps
•	Windows → desktop
👉 One Line:
Linux is preferred for servers, Windows for desktop. 

