📂 1. Basic Commands (System + Navigation)
pwd                         # current path
ls                             # list files
ls -l                          # details
ls -a                         # hidden files
cd dir                      # enter directory
cd ..                         # back
cd ~                        # home
tree                         # folder structure (install: apt install tree)
hostname                # system name
cat /etc/os-release   # OS info
which command     # command path
history                    # commands history
________________________________________
📁 2. File & Directory Commands
🔹 File Create & Edit
touch file.txt        # empty file create karna (fast editor)
cat > file.txt        # file create + content likhna (overwrite)
cat file.txt          # file ka content dekhna
cat >> file.txt       # existing file me content add (append)
nano file.txt         # easy editor (create/edit file)
vi file.txt           # advanced editor (create/edit file)
🔹 File Operations 
cp a.txt b.txt        # file copy karna
cp -r dir1 dir2       # directory ko copy karna
mv a.txt b.txt        # file rename ya move karna
rm file.txt           # file delete karna
rmdir folder          # empty folder delete karna
rm -r folder          # folder + andar ka data delete karna
🔹 File View 
less file.txt         # file scroll k sath dekhna
head file.txt         # first 10 lines dekhna
tail file.txt         # last 10 lines dekhna
tail -f file.txt      # live file updates dekhna (logs)
🔹 Directory Commands
mkdir devops          # new folder create karna
________________________________________

🌐 3. Networking Commands
ip a
👉 Tumhare system ka IP address aur network info dikhata hai
💡 (Jaise: server ka address kya hai)
ping google.com
👉 Check karta hai internet ya kisi server se connection hai ya nahi
💡 (Jaise: network chal raha hai ya down hai)
curl URL
👉 Kisi website/API se data uthata hai (background me)
💡 (Jaise: API test karna ya response dekhna)
wget URL
👉 Internet se file download karta hai
💡 (Jaise: software ya script download karna)
netstat -tulnp
👉 System pe kaunse ports open hain + kaunsa service chal rahi hai
💡 (Jaise: nginx port 80 pe run ho raha hai ya nahi)
ss -lntp
👉 Same kaam as netstat (modern + fast)
💡 (Ports aur running services check karna)
________________________________________
⚙️ 4. Other Important Commands
🔹 Package Management
apt update                      #  system ki package list update karta hai (latest info laata hai)
apt install package         # koi bhi software install karna (Ubuntu)
🔹 Services
systemctl start nginx          # service start karna (nginx chalu)
systemctl restart nginx       # service restart (issue fix ya reload)
systemctl status nginx        # service chal rahi hai ya nahi check
🔹 Processes
Ps                            # current running processes list
Top                         # live system usage (CPU, RAM) dekhna                  :for exit q
Htop                       # top ka advanced + easy version                                : for exit f10
kill PID                  # normal tareeke se process band karna
kill -9 PID              # force se process kill karna (jab na rukay)
🔹 Disk Usage
Df -h      # system ki total disk space aur free space check
du -sh     # kisi folder ka size check
🔹 Logs
Journalctl                             # system ke logs (history + errors) dekhna
tail -f /var/log/syslog           # live logs dekhna (real-time updates)
🔹 Users & Groups
useradd devuser                                # naya user create
id username                                      # user verify krna
passwd devuser                                 # user ka password set
groupadd devgroup                           # naya group create
getent group groupname                   # verify group
gpasswd -a devuser devgroup           # user ko group me add
🔹 Useful Commands
echo "text"                                           # text screen pe print karna
echo "hello" > file.txt                     # create + content add
echo "hello" >> file.txt             # File me naya content add (append) karega
grep "word" file                       # file me specific word search
sort file.txt                               # file ka data sort (A-Z) means File ke data ko line by line arrange
tar -cvf backup.tar folder/       # folder ka backup (archive) banana
gzip file.txt                             # file ko compress (size kam) karna
